FBIS4-18550 "drweu067_b_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-067 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 BENELUX COUNTRIES Belgium Rwandan Ambassador `Shocked' by Attack on Presidents Rwandan Ambassador `Shocked' by Attack on Presidents LD0704082794 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 0700 GMT 7 Apr 94 LD0704082794 Brussels La Une Radio Network French BFN [Text] The situation is very confused in Kigali. This is why the Rwandan ambassador in Brussels reacted very cautiously: [Ambassador] I am deeply shocked by this barbaric act which took the lives of Major General Juvenal Habyarimana, president of the Rwandan Republic; Mr Cyprien Ntaryamira, president of the Republic of Burundi; and their aides who were accompanying them. I am very worried about the situation and I would like to express my indignation. I also want to say that I hope the Rwandan people will be able to overcome the hardship they are experiencing now. [Announcer] The Rwandan ambassador in Brussels was interviewed a few minutes ago by Francois Vouarnac.
